                      <item xml:id="a01">
                      <desc type="Asmat">
                      <locus target="#192v"/> Asmat prayer for protection against wild animals
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                      <item xml:id="a02"><desc><locus target="#ir(ecto)"/>“(19)41 EC, Tahsas 13”</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e01"><desc><locus target="#iv(erso) #iir(ecto)"/> blank</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a03"><desc><locus target="#iiv(erso)"/>, top 9 lines: Feast days of the Apostles and Evangelists. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a04"><desc><locus target="#ii v(erso)"/>, lines 10ff: Best days of the year on which to lay a foundation so that it is not eaten by termites. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a05"><desc><locus target="# 164v–165r"/>, top margin: Concluding prayer for the psalms. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a06"><desc type="GuestText"><locus target="#173r"/> Concluding prayer for <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT2277salotu#Moses1"/>. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a07"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="# 165r and 173r"/> name of owner: Akalä Sellasie. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a08"><desc><locus target="#173v"/>, top five lines: note in a later hand: “In the name of the father and the son and Holy Spirit, one God, conqueror and Lion of the tribe of Judah, Mǝnilǝk II, appointed by God King of Kings of Ethiopia.” </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e02"><desc><locus target="#173v"/>in pencil, illegible.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e03"><desc>Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters for some of the sections.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e04"><desc>
                        words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#24r #40r #41v #44r"/>, etc.);
                        and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#4v #8v #9v #14r"/>, etc.);
                        text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#4v #13v #62v #172v"/>)</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e05">
                        <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                          appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe
                          reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout). This scribe also will complete the line of
                          text above the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#103v #120r #120v"/>)</desc></item>
                    </list>
